OL,3,COne in four fear having to turn off
OL,4,Cheating and hot water this winter `
OL,5,Csurvey
OL,7,FThe charity, which is still supporting
OL,8,Frecord numbers of people with energy
OL,9,Fdebt despite lower costs in the summer
OL,10,Fmonths, said households "will continue
OL,11,Fto face impossible choices and drastic
OL,12,Fcutbacks to be able to heat their
OL,13,Fhomes" without urgent Government
OL,14,Fintervention.
OL,16,FOverall, the survey found that 48% of
OL,17,Frespondents said they would have to
OL,18,Fturn down or turn off their heating or
OL,19,Fwater if the energy price cap rises by
OL,20,Fthe 9% predicted by experts.
